Package: PhysiMineR
Type: Package
Title: Extraction, Cleaning and Analysis of Upper GI Physiological Data
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: person(
    given  = "Sebastian",
    family = "Zeki",
    role   = c("aut", "cre"),
    email  = "sebastian.zeki@nhs.net"
  )
Description: Tools for importing, cleaning, classifying and analysing
    upper gastrointestinal physiological test data, including
    high-resolution manometry (HRM), ambulatory pH-impedance monitoring,
    and wireless pH capsule (BRAVO) studies.
    Acid reflux is classified according to the Lyon Consensus 2.0 criteria
    (Gyawali et al., 2021) and oesophageal motility is diagnosed according
    to the Chicago Classification version 4.0 (Yadlapati et al., 2021).
